{
  "stem": "24163.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "So somebody-- we don't even know, to this day, who-- took him to Essen where they had some major hospitals.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And there he was for several days.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "Now, my folks realized, at that time, the urgency of leaving Germany.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "And we had all registered for visas to go to the United States.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "But as I-- as I indicated earlier, there was a waiting period.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "And we probably had to wait at least another year, until our number, they called it, our number came up at the German-- at the American consulate, so we could get our visa.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "But my parents, who had sent my brother earlier on, a year prior, to the United States on a children's transport, kindertransport, then said, you have to get out, no matter what.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "Because I was 17 years of age, and they were picking up boys my age.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "They were picking them up on the streets.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And you never saw them again.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "They were gone.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "You can't stay here.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "They know you are here.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "You can't stay here.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "You've got to get out.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they made efforts and were able to get me on a train that left with the-- this kindertransport also to Holland, with all children under the age of 18.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But prior to that, I had to obtain, from the German government, releases that all my taxes were paid, my social security was paid, all the documents that you needed in order to get a visa to leave Germany.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I-- I went to the tax bureau, the [GERMAN], they called it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I went to the social security office.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And as I walked into the social security office, which is called the [GERMAN] in German, there was a young man my age behind the counter.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
